# 🎮 Tic-Tac-Toe in Python

A terminal-based implementation of the classic Tic-Tac-Toe game with clean visuals and simple controls.


## Features
- 🖥️ Clean terminal interface
- 🔄 Player turn switching (X and O)
- ✅ Input validation
- 🏆 Win detection (rows, columns, diagonals)
- 🤝 Tie detection
- 🧹 Screen clearing between moves

## How to Run
1. Ensure you have Python 3 installed
2. Clone this repository or copy the code
3. Run the game:
```bash
python tictactoe.py
Game Controls
Enter numbers 1-9 to make moves:

Copy
 1 | 2 | 3
-----------
 4 | 5 | 6
-----------
 7 | 8 | 9
Requirements
Python 3.x

os module (included in standard library)

Example Gameplay
bash
Copy
Player X's turn
Enter position (1-9): 5

   |   |  
-----------
   | X |  
-----------
   |   |  

Player O's turn
Enter position (1-9): 1

 O |   |  
-----------
   | X |  
-----------
   |   |  
Customization Options
Change player symbols:

python
Copy
current_player = "X"  # Change to any symbol
Modify the board appearance:

python
Copy
print(f"""
 {board[0]} | {board[1]} | {board[2]}
-----------
 {board[3]} | {board[4]} | {board[5]}
-----------
 {board[6]} | {board[7]} | {board[8]}
""")
Troubleshooting
If the screen doesn't clear properly, try:

On Windows: Use cls command

On Mac/Linux: Use clear command

Future Improvements
